> These, friends, are not your average pork chops. In fact, our chefs gave 'em a steak-like treatment, transforming the everyday protein into something above and beyond. The chops are seared to perfection, then drizzled with an ultra-savory, rosemary-flecked pan sauce. The sides? Just as impressive. We're serving up creamy mashed potatoes and roasted carrots and onion wedges to round everything out. Prepare for a flavor explosion.

== Roasted Vegetables ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @Parsnip{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @Red Onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Toss carrots, parsnips, and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, @salt, and @pepper.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

== Pork Chops ==

Meanwhile, pat @Pork Chops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with @salt and @pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, strip @Rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (3 tsp for 4 servings).

== Rosemary Demi-Glace ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add minced onion and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring often, until onion is softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @Chicken Demi-Glace{1} and @water{¼%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted.

== To Serve ==

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork and veggies between plates. Top pork with sauce and serve.